<table class="contentpaneopen">



<tr>
<td valign="top">
<p><img height="273" width="300" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-training.jpg" alt="eden-training" style="float: right;" /><strong>We offer a selection of standard training courses which include:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Managing the day-to-day</strong> – to identify the difference between leadership and management tasks, and the different styles of leadership and appropriate uses. It looks at managing conflict and explores the impact of change on teams and strategies to manage it.</p>
<p><strong>Managing self & time</strong> – how to ensure you get the best out of your time at work, allow thinking time and be able to manage yourself to achieve great results. Some hints and tips as to how to ensure you control your day as far as possible. Also looks at procrastination, delegation, stress management and diary management.</p>
<p><strong>Planning & decision making (be right, plan right, do it right!)</strong> – understanding the importance of planning, this workshop explores how best to plan and organise on a day-to-day and medium term basis; explores the process of making great, well-informed decisions and tools that can help in this; the impact of bad planning and decision making; how to challenge up/down and the impact this has on others.</p>
<p><strong>Problem solving (be a solver not a poser)</strong> – In order to present a solution and not pose a problem this workshop identifies the different types of thinking when problem solving among individuals; practise skills and techniques to analyse a problem; how to generate solutions;  how to implement, monitor and use contingency planning techniques; getting buy-in for decisions; basic project management skills.</p>
<p><strong>Building successful teams</strong> - understanding the dynamics of a team, and how to get the best out of the different roles individuals play within their immediate team, and/or wider departmental team. Looking at what makes a successful team, and how each person can impact on the success moving forward.</p>
<p><strong>Powerful presence</strong> - a very practical, hands-on workshop on presentation skills and how to engage with your audience with a WOW impact, which allows you to be more confident in your ability to present and engage with your audience.</p>
<p><strong>Coaching skills for managers</strong> - this is a practical approach, with a process that’s easy to remember in order to encourage a coaching approach to management. Looking at coaching as a topic and understanding the difference between coaching, mentoring, counselling, management and how coaching can have a positive impact on producing results. This 2 day workshop is suitable for anybody who is responsible for managing a team of any size or who wants to find out more about coaching. This can be run as two separate days also.</p>
<p><strong>Building better relationships</strong> – an introduction to emotional intelligence in the workplace using Daniel Goleman's EQ framework. This module allows individuals to explore themselves, how they impact on others, how they manage their emotions and how they can adapt their social skills to have a positive impact on people they come into contact with.  This workshop is suitable for anyone who wishes to understand how to manage relationships astutely. This workshop can be run as 1 or 2 days.</p>
<p><strong>People & change</strong> - in our ever-changing environment, this workshops looks at the impact change has on individuals and the team. The workshop offers tools, structure and models to support managers in understanding it, managing it and leading the team through it. It also allows individuals to identify coping techniques during this difficult time.</p>
<p><strong>1st class feedback</strong> – understanding the importance of feedback and how to have a feedback discussion. Tips and techniques to ensure that you are confident in delivering feedback so that it “lands” the right way each and every time. Also, once you have feedback what do you do with it and how it can link into your own personal development and growth.</p>
<p><strong>Hunger for learning</strong> – a workshop to really harness the desire to want to learn and grow as an individual. Using the Career Wheel start to identify where you are today, and where you want to be in this busy, manic society. It captures why having a hunger for learning is so important in this very competitive business world.</p>
<p><strong>Managing our people better</strong> - How to Hold a Disciplinary/Grievance discussion - a practical look at the pitfalls managers can fall into, when having to enforce/follow the disciplinary/grievance process. It touches on Employment Law and gives best practice advice on how to manage, these sometimes difficult, discussions. Raises the awareness of managers as to what they need to be aware of to work within employment law</p>
<p><strong>Confidence from within</strong> – a workshop filled with lots of hints, tips and techniques to becoming more confident from the inside out. Confidence is not something we are born either with or without, but we are all capable of feeling more confident and this workshop shows you how to make that happen.</p>
<p><strong>Recruitment & selection</strong> – a workshop which aids you with the tools to enable you to select the right candidates for your business. Covering aspects of equality and diversity, interview questioning styles, communication techniques, legal process, through to induction.</p>
<p><strong>Understanding employment law</strong> – a workshop which integrates basic employment law knowledge and understanding, into practical tips of implementation to ensure compliance.</p>
<p><strong>Appraisal skills for managers –</strong> a practical workshop that informs managers on how to conduct an effective appraisal, and to achieve the desired outcomes. The workshop gives managers a safe environment to practice their skills at handling an appraisal, or performance feedback meeting. Equipping managers with skills and tips on effective communication when giving and receiving feedback on performance</p>
<p><strong>Appraisal skills for employees</strong> – a practical workshop that informs employees on how to conduct an effective appraisal and to achieve the desired outcomes. The workshop gives employees a safe environment to practice their skills at handling an appraisal or performance feedback meeting. Equipping staff with skills and tips on effective communication when giving and receiving feedback on performance</p>
<p><strong>Equality & diversity awareness</strong> –  looking at, in depth, the importance of managing people in a fair and consistent manner is important if you are managing people. This workshop shows you how to provide a practical application to your policies and procedures and allows you to understand the legal requirements that fall within being an equal and diverse employer.</p>
<p><strong>Interviewing skills – </strong>a key skill for all managers to master, in order to recruit the best of the best.  Gaining an understanding of great questions, active listening and great communication skills, this workshop gives you the opportunity to practice your skills in a safe environment. You will also learn how a competency based approach to interviewing gives you a robust outcome, and allows you to select the right person for the job. We also touch on person and job specifications, taking notes and how recruitment assessments can be used when recruiting.</p>
<p><strong>Practical implementation of family friendly legislation and best practice</strong> – a practical workshop that shows you how to best use and implement a family friendly approach within your business. We look at the different types of Family Friendly policies and legislation surrounding them and how to encourage best practice at all times<span style="text-decoration: underline;">.</span></p>
<p><strong>Effective communication</strong>- a workshop that recognises the importance of communication at work and how to use effective engagement techniques. Looking at your own personal style of communication and its impact and the effects of good/poor communication on a team. Concentrating on non-verbal communication is a key part of this workshop, as is feedback on your style and how you can ensure you have a great impact on all who you communicate with.</p>
<p><strong>Understanding emotional intelligence</strong> – in our current “world of work” you have to be both intellectually and emotionally intelligent. This workshops looks at the concept of emotional intelligence and the impact it can have on you and others around you. A must for every business manager who has contact with people.</p>
<p><strong>Goal setting and achievement</strong> <strong>–</strong> we don’t often get the chance to stop and reflect on what we really want in our working and personal lives, and this workshop gives you the opportunity to take that “pit stop” and look at where you are now, and where you want to be, with practical advice, guidance and tools to help you achieve your hopes and dreams.</p>
<p><strong>Commercial awareness</strong> – In this workshop we will explore an ever increasingly important aspect of management; being commercially aware. This means that rather than just doing a job, making decisions and accepting the results, you are able to see the bigger picture, work not just efficiently but profitably too, maintaining healthy relationships both internal and external to your business and generating creative solutions to everyday business challenges. Especially in tough economic climates, these abilities pay dividends by keeping you and your business competitive and with a leading edge. Areas covered in this workshop include - understanding why commercial awareness is a crucial element of knowledge and skill for a manager today,  increasing knowledge around basic financial accounting, demonstrating the application of Return on Investment, planning how to make best use of a budget, managing your internal and external relationships and applying creativity to produce competitive and leading edge solutions within your available resources</p>
<p><strong>Team member to team manager</strong> - this workshop gives individuals who are new to management, or about to be promoted to a management position, an understanding of the role of the front/first line manager. It gives a foundation in the skills of understanding responsibilities, motivation and leading from the front, communication, planning and organising, analytical skills and managing the day to day. This workshop is suitable for newly appointed managers and those wanting to refresh their existing skill set.</p>
<p><strong>The 1<sup>st</sup> 90 days</strong> – is key to people joining a business as to how they go about finding out about a new company, networking, stakeholder mapping and producing results in the first 90 days. This workshop can also be tailored for managers in how they can manage individuals during the 1st 90 days and what their responsibilities and expectations are.</p>
<p><strong>Managing conflict</strong> – this is something that no-one really likes, but by raising your awareness as to what conflict is, how to manage it and recognising individual styles and ways of dealing with conflict, you can adapt your behaviour in order to manage conflict in a positive and constructive way. This practical workshop looks at assertiveness, drivers and conflict styles and gives you the tools and techniques in managing these, in order to create a win-win every time.</p>
<p>If you have not found a course that meets your needs, or would like training on a number of combined topics, please contact us to discuss how we can cater for your specific requirements.</p></td>
</tr>

